"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}, {\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8320413056720383e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There have been a succession of issues that have been badly handled from a communication point of view,\\\" said Philippe Moreau Chevrolet, a lecturer in communication at Sciences Po university in Paris and the founder of the MCBG Conseil public relations agency.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Moreau\", \"score\": 0.4506317107272318, \"rank\": 0.6199794082868836, \"text\": \"Moreau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Moreau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Moreau\"}, {\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet\", \"score\": 0.9992740088363085, \"rank\": 0.0007255310576381044, \"text\": \"Chevrolet\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chevrolet\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sciences_Po\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sciences Po university\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sciences_Po\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sciences_Po\"}, {\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8320413056720383e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a succession\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"a communication point\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"view\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"a lecturer\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"communication\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"the MCBG Conseil public relations agency\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Instead of getting people behind the Games, they have created mistrust.\\\"\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"mistrust\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's association of hoteliers and restaurant owners issued an unusual statement earlier in January, condemning French politicians for their \\\"anxiety-inducing\\\" announcements around the Games and urging them to come together.\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 2039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9579291103760884, \"rank\": 0.03791431880673877, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9989523057643498, \"rank\": 0.0009813069967032695, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hoteliers\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurant owners\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"an unusual statement\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1895}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"their \\\"anxiety-inducing\\\" announcements\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In general, we would strongly urge all of our public authorities, collectively and with solidarity, to speak positively and responsibly,\\\" the statement added.\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our public authorities\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"solidarity\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the statement\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other recent complaints centre on the construction work that snares traffic daily around the capital, while resentment lingers over the handling of ticket sales in 2023 that saw many locals priced out.\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other recent complaints centre\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the construction work\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"resentment\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"the handling\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"ticket sales\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"many locals\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris will see \\\"the most expensive ticket prices in an athletics arena that we have witnessed at an Olympic Games\\\", said World Athletics president Sebastian Coe in December, adding he was worried the families of some athletes would be unable to attend.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2405, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8320413056720383e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5837963048664949e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most expensive ticket prices\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"an athletics arena\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2475}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"December\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"the families\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2613}, {\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 organisers remain confident that sights such as beach volleyball in front of the Eiffel Tower, swimming in the River Seine, or the marathon through the capital's fabled streets will lift spirits once the flame is lit on July 26.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"sights\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"beach volleyball\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2734}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2743}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2763}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's fabled streets\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2846}, {\"ngram\": \"spirits\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2864}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They make a distinction between the often noisy and attention-seeking media and political debate, and wider public opinion.\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 3023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a distinction\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"the often noisy and attention-seeking media\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"political debate\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 2996}, {\"ngram\": \"wider public opinion\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A survey by the Odoxa group for RTL radio in November suggested that 65 per cent of French people were in favour of the Games - a fall of 11 points in two years but still a large majority with positive views.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3109, \"end\": 3122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A survey\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"the Odoxa group\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"RTL radio\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3066}, {\"ngram\": \"November\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3078}, {\"ngram\": \"65 per cent\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3137}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3150}, {\"ngram\": \"11 points\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3172}, {\"ngram\": \"two years\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"positive views\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Paris region, slightly more than half of people were in favour.\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3242, \"end\": 3247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8320413056720383e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"slightly more than half\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3279}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3283, \"to\": 3289}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers also point to the orderly preparations, as well as their budget restraint in comparison with other modern editions.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3433, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3317}, {\"ngram\": \"the orderly preparations\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"their budget restraint\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3391}, {\"ngram\": \"comparison\", \"from\": 3395, \"to\": 3405}, {\"ngram\": \"other modern editions\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the sporting infrastructure is finished.\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sporting infrastructure\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes' village is almost ready to be furnished.\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The athletes' village\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crucial metro and train line extensions will be ready in time, they insist.\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Crucial metro and train line extensions\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 35